    "recap_url": "https://www.upstatespartans.com/news/2026/3/18/baseball-fights-back-pushing-across-go-ahead-run-in-the-ninth-in-an-11-10-midweek-victory-at-charlotte",
    "recap_headline": "University of South Carolina Upstate Athletics",
    "recap_text": "CHARLOTTE, N.C. \u2013\nStarting a five-game road swing with a game feeling more like a Spring Training contest than a college baseball game, USC Upstate baseball rallied multiple times, erasing a deficit that had grown as large as five runs with clutch runs in the late innings in an 11-10 victory Wednesday at Charlotte.\nUsing 10 pitchers against the 49ers, the Spartans' bullpen allowed just two runs from the third inning onward, putting Upstate in position for its comeback in the ninth inning. Six relievers, freshman right-handed pitcher\nAndrew Kummer\n, junior righty\nNathan Hook\n, junior left-hander\nJack Gibson\n, sophomore southpaw\nMax Kaplan\n, freshman righty\nBen Chuttey\n, and redshirt freshman right-hander\nJacob Kirby\n, turned in scoreless outings.\nTossing a scoreless eighth inning, Chuttey registered his first career victory before Kirby shut the door in the ninth to record his second save of the season.\nHeading the effort at the plate, redshirt sophomore shortstop\nMaloy Heaghney\ncollected a career-high six RBI as both of his hits went for extra bases, a first-inning, three-run homer and a two-run double in the third. Redshirt sophomore centerfielder\nHenry Zenor\nnotched the Spartans' other multi-RBI night, driving home the tying runs in both the seventh and ninth innings.\nRedshirt senior third baseman\nJake Armsey\ndrove home the go-ahead run in the ninth, lacing a single inside the third base bag. Fifth-year senior first baseman\nJohnny Sweeney\nand redshirt freshman leftfielder\nTrey Bentley\neach tallied an RBI for the Spartans.\nGame Information\nScore: USC Upstate 11; Charlotte 10\nRecords: USC Upstate (11-11; 2-1 Big South); Charlotte (14-7; 0-0 American)\nLocation: Hayes Stadium | Charlotte, N.C.\nHow It Happened\nT1: For the second time in three games,\nMaloy Heaghney\ngets the game's scoring started with a three-run shot to left, his third home run of the year.\nB1: Getting a pair of runs back, Charlotte's Dylan Koontz slugged a two-run home run to right-center.\nB2: Fighting back to take the advantage, Charlotte sent 12 hitters to the plate, using seven hits to score six runs. Todd Hudson recorded the biggest hit for the 49ers in the frame, a two-run, go-ahead home run.\nT3: Battling back, Upstate scratched three tallies in the third, doing so behind a pair of doubles coming from\nJohnny Sweeney\nand Heaghney. Heaghney's double drove home two, giving him a career-high five RBI through his first two at-bats.\nT4: Pulling the Spartans within a run,\nTrey Bentley\ndrove home a run with a single to center in his first at-bat of the day, scoring\nHenry Zenor\n.\nB4: Taking advantage of a wild pitch, Charlotte added an insurance run in the fourth.\nT6: Following a sac bunt from Bentley to push two runners into scoring position, Heaghney recorded RBI number six of the day with a groundout to third.\nT7: Punching a ball inside third base and down the leftfield line, Zenor tied the game as he drove home\nPreston Lucas\nfrom second.\nB7: Taking advantage of a failed pickoff attempt and a fielding error in center, Charlotte regained the advantage as Adrian Jimenez scored in the frame.\nT9: Punching back one final time, Zenor tied the game again in the ninth as he ripped a single through the right side.\nJake Armsey\ndelivered the go-ahead run for Upstate as he tucked a ball inside the third base line, sending\nKenan Bowman\nracing home.\nNotable\nDriving home five runs across his first two plate appearances and six total runs on the day,\nMaloy Heaghney's\ncareer-high total makes him the second Spartan with a five-plus RBI game this season. His six RBI surpass\nJake Armsey's\nfive RBI against Western Carolina on Feb. 17 for the most in a game by a Spartan this season.\nGunning down a runner at the plate in the third inning,\nKenan Bowman\nrecorded his team-best sixth outfield assist of 2026. His outfield assist total is the best for a Spartan since Koby Kropf totaled eight in 2024.\nUp Next for the Spartans\nFor the first time in Big South play, USC Upstate hits the road, continuing its five-game road swing with a three-game set at Longwood. The Spartans and Lancers face off Friday at 6:00 p.m. ET, Saturday at 3:00 p.m., and Sunday at 1:00 p.m.\nConnect with the Spartans\nFacebook.com/UpstateAthletics\nTwitter | @UpstateBSB | @UpstateSpartans\nInstagram | @UpstateBSB | @UpstateSpartans\nYouTube.com/UpstateSpartans\nINVEST IN CHAMPIONS\n- Join the Upstate Athletic Fund (UAF) and enjoy enhanced benefits for your support of all USC Upstate programs! Make your gift today,\nclick here\n!"
